в•ӯв”Җ assistant [MainThread@2256878] в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•®
в”Ӯ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The user wants me to fix a crash in the LLVM SLP vectorizer.                                                                                                                             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The crash is a verifier error: `Instruction does not dominate all uses!`. This indicates that the SLP vectorizer is generating invalid LLVM IR. The problem arises when vectorizing      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ instructions whose operands are defined in different basic blocks. The vectorizer must place newly generated instructions in a basic block that dominates all their uses.                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The error message points to a dominance issue with an `insertelement` instruction. This suggests that the SLP vectorizer is not correctly determining the insertion point for            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ instructions that build up the vectors, especially when operands come from different basic blocks.                                                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ Looking at the provided LLVM IR, we can see multiple PHI nodes at the `._crit_edge` block, gathering values from different control flow paths. The SLP vectorizer is attempting to       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ vectorize these PHI nodes and the operations that feed into them. The operands `%1` and `%2` are defined in the entry block `.thread`, while other operands like `%8` and `%10` are      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ defined in block `6`.                                                                                                                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ When the vectorizer tries to create a vector from scalars defined in different blocks, it needs to find a suitable insertion point. A common strategy is to use the common dominator of  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ the blocks containing the scalar operands. However, if an instruction is hoisted too high up the dominator tree, it might be placed before the definition of one of its operands,        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ leading to an invalid module.                                                                                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The problem seems to be in the logic that determines the insertion point for vectorized instructions. Specifically, when building a vector from scalar operands, the insertion point for в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ the vector-building instructions (like `insertelement`) must be dominated by the definitions of all scalar operands.                                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ A potential fix is to ensure that the insertion point for any new instruction is not only a common dominator of the uses but is also dominated by the definitions of all its operands.   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ In the context of the SLP vectorizer, when building a vector, the insertion point for the vector construction sequence should be the instruction's basic block if all operands are       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ available there. If operands come from different blocks, the insertion point must be carefully chosen to respect dominance.                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The `getInsertPoint` function in `SLPVectorizer.cpp` is a likely candidate for the source of this bug. It's responsible for determining where to place new instructions. The logic might в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ be too aggressive in hoisting instructions.                                                                                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ A common pattern for fixing such bugs is to ensure that for any new instruction, its insertion point is dominated by the definitions of all its operands. This can be done by computing  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ the common dominator of the operand-defining blocks and the original insertion point, and then ensuring the final insertion point is dominated by all operand definitions. A simpler,    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ more robust approach is to iterate through all operands of a new instruction and update the insertion point to be dominated by each operand's definition.                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ I will modify the `getInsertPoint` function in `lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp`. I'll add logic to ensure that the chosen insertion point for a new instruction is dominated в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ by the definitions of all its scalar operands. This will prevent the verifier error by guaranteeing that no instruction is used before it is defined.                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The change will involve:                                                                                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 1.  In `getInsertPoint`, after determining an initial insertion point `IP`.                                                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 2.  Iterating through the scalar operands of the instruction being vectorized.                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 3.  For each operand that is an `Instruction`, finding its parent basic block.                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 4.  Using `DT.findNearestCommonDominator` to update `IP`'s block to be dominated by the operand's block.                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 5.  This ensures the final insertion point is valid with respect to all operands.                                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ sed -i '1009a\                                                                                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   // Make sure that the chosen insertion point is dominated by all operands.\                                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   // This is important for vectorizing instructions with operands from different\                                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   // basic blocks.\                                                                                                                                                                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   for (Value *V : VL) {\                                                                                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ     if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {\                                                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       if (I->getParent() != Block) {\                                                                                                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         if (auto *NewBlock = DT.findNearestCommonDominator(Block, I->getParent())) {\                                                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ           Block = NewBlock;\                                                                                                                                                             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         } else {\                                                                                                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ           return nullptr;\                                                                                                                                                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         }\                                                                                                                                                                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       }\                                                                                                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ     }\                                                                                                                                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   }\                                                                                                                                                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ' lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                                                                                             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      в”Ӯ
