в”Ӯ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ I have analyzed the crash and the provided LLVM IR. The crash is a verifier error, `Instruction does not dominate all uses!`, which happens during the SLP vectorization pass. This      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ indicates that the SLP vectorizer is generating invalid IR by placing an instruction at a location where it does not dominate all of its uses.                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The reproducer IR shows a complex control flow graph with multiple PHI nodes in the `._crit_edge` block. These PHI nodes gather values from different predecessor blocks. The SLP        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ vectorizer attempts to vectorize these PHI nodes and their dependent computations. The operands of the PHIs come from different basic blocks (e.g., `%1` and `%2` from `.thread`, `%8`   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ and `%10` from `6`).                                                                                                                                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ When the SLP vectorizer creates vector instructions (like `insertelement` or `shufflevector`), it needs to find a suitable insertion point. This insertion point must dominate all uses  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ of the new instruction. The bug likely lies in the logic that determines this insertion point, specifically in the `getInsertPoint` function within `SLPVectorizer.cpp`.                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The error message `Instruction does not dominate all uses!` suggests that the problem is not about an instruction's operands not being available (which would be an "operand does not    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ dominate use" error), but rather that the newly created instruction itself is not placed correctly relative to its own users.                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The existing `getInsertPoint` function in `SLPVectorizer.cpp` calculates a common dominator for the basic blocks of the scalar values being vectorized (`VL`) and then for the basic     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ blocks of all their users. This determines the basic block for the insertion. Then, it finds the first instruction in that block that is a user of any of the scalars in `VL` and        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ inserts the new vector instruction before it.                                                                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The problem arises when the chosen insertion block is a successor of one of the user's blocks in the dominator tree. If the insertion block is the same as a user's block, inserting     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ before the user is correct. However, if the insertion block is a successor, the new instruction will not dominate the user in the predecessor block.                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ To fix this, I will modify `getInsertPoint`. After computing the common dominator block (`Block`) for all scalar definitions and uses, I will add a check. If the chosen `Block` is not  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ the same as the block of a user instruction (`I->getParent()`), it means the user is in a different block. In this case, the insertion point must be at the end of the user's block      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ (`I->getParent()->getTerminator()`) to ensure dominance. This is because `Block` is a common dominator, so any path from the user's block must pass through `Block`. Placing the         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ instruction at the end of the user's block ensures it's executed before control transfers to `Block` or any other successor.                                                             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ I will use `sed` to insert this logic into `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp`. The change will be within the loop that iterates over the users of the scalar values.      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ sed -i '1028i\                                                                                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       if (Block != I->getParent()) {\                                                                                                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         IP = I->getParent()->getTerminator();\                                                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         continue;\                                                                                                                                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       }\                                                                                                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      в”Ӯ
