в”Ӯ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The user wants me to fix a crash in the LLVM SLP vectorizer. The crash is a verifier error: `Instruction does not dominate all uses!`. This indicates that the SLP vectorizer is         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ generating invalid LLVM IR.                                                                                                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The provided LLVM IR shows a complex control flow graph where the SLP vectorizer attempts to vectorize PHI nodes that gather values from different control flow paths. Specifically, it  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ tries to vectorize `lcssa` PHI nodes in the `._crit_edge` block. Some operands for these PHIs are defined in the entry block (`.thread`), while others are defined in a different block  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ (`6`).                                                                                                                                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The vectorizer identifies a group of scalar instructions to vectorize. When these instructions are in different basic blocks, it must find a common dominator block to place the new     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ vectorized instructions. The problem arises when an operand of a new instruction is not defined in a block that dominates the insertion point.                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The error `Instruction does not dominate all uses!` suggests that the newly created instruction is placed in a block that does not dominate one of its uses. However, the stack trace    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ points to a verifier error, and the message `Instruction does not dominate all uses!` is often a symptom of an operand not dominating its use. The verifier checks for this.             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The root cause is likely in the logic that determines the insertion point for new instructions. The function `getInsertPoint` in `SLPVectorizer.cpp` is responsible for this. It         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ calculates a common dominator for the blocks of the scalar values being vectorized. If this calculation is not careful enough, it can select an insertion point that is not dominated by в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ the definition of one of the operands.                                                                                                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ A robust fix is to ensure that the chosen insertion point is dominated by the definitions of all operands. I will modify `getInsertPoint` to enforce this. After calculating an initial  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ insertion block, I will iterate through all the scalar values that are part of the vectorization. If a scalar is an `Instruction`, I will find its parent basic block and use the        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `DominatorTree` to find the nearest common dominator of the current insertion block and the operand's block. This ensures the final insertion block is dominated by all operand          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ definitions.                                                                                                                                                                             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ I previously failed to locate the file and then used an incorrect line number. I have now determined the correct path is `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp`. I will now   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ apply the patch at the correct location within the `getInsertPoint` function. The logic should be inserted after the initial `Block` is determined but before `IP` is calculated.        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ sed -i '1009a\                                                                                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   // Make sure that the chosen insertion point is dominated by all operands.\                                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   // This is important for vectorizing instructions with operands from different\                                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   // basic blocks.\                                                                                                                                                                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   for (Value *V : VL) {\                                                                                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ     if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {\                                                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       if (I->getParent() != Block) {\                                                                                                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         if (auto *NewBlock = DT.findNearestCommonDominator(Block, I->getParent())) {\                                                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ           Block = NewBlock;\                                                                                                                                                             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         } else {\                                                                                                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ           return nullptr;\                                                                                                                                                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         }\                                                                                                                                                                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       }\                                                                                                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
