в”Ӯ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The user wants me to fix a crash in the LLVM SLP vectorizer. The crash is a verifier error, `Instruction does not dominate all uses!`, which indicates that the vectorizer is generating в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ invalid LLVM IR. My previous attempts failed due to compilation errors caused by placing the patch in the wrong location within `SLPVectorizer.cpp`. The variables needed for my fix     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ (`VL`, `Block`, `DT`) were not in scope at the insertion point.                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The problem lies in determining the correct insertion point for new vector instructions, especially when operands come from different basic blocks. The insertion point must be          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ dominated by the definitions of all operands. The function responsible for this is `SLPVectorizer::getInsertPoint`.                                                                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ My plan is to modify `SLPVectorizer::getInsertPoint` to correctly calculate the insertion block. The current implementation has a flaw where it might select a block that is not         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ dominated by all operand definitions.                                                                                                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The correct logic should be:                                                                                                                                                             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 1.  Find the common dominator of all basic blocks containing the scalar values to be vectorized (`VL`).                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 2.  This common dominator block is the earliest valid point for the insertion.                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 3.  Then, consider the users of these scalar values to potentially move the insertion point further down, closer to the uses.                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ I will replace the existing, flawed logic for determining the initial `Block` with a correct implementation. I will find the start of the `getInsertPoint` function and insert a new     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ block of code that correctly computes the common dominator of all operand blocks. This new code will iterate through `VL`, find the parent block for each instruction operand, and use   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `DT.findNearestCommonDominator` to find a block that dominates all of them. This will be our new, correct `Block`. I will then delete the old, incorrect logic.                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ To avoid the previous errors, I will use a very specific `sed` command that targets the function signature `Instruction *SLPVectorizer::getInsertPoint(ArrayRef<Value *> VL) const {` to в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ensure the patch is placed correctly.                                                                                                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ sed -i '/^Instruction \*SLPVectorizer::getInsertPoint(ArrayRef<Value \*> VL) const {$/a\                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   BasicBlock *Block = nullptr;\                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   for (Value *V : VL) {\                                                                                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ     if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {\                                                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       if (!Block)\                                                                                                                                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         Block = I->getParent();\                                                                                                                                                         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       else\                                                                                                                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         Block = DT.findNearestCommonDominator(Block, I->getParent());\                                                                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ     }\                                                                                                                                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   }\                                                                                                                                                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && \                                                                                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ sed -i '/BasicBlock \*Block = getSameBlock(VL);/,/^\s*} else {$/d' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && \                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ sed -i 's/Block = UserBlock;/if (UserBlock) Block = DT.findNearestCommonDominator(Block, UserBlock);/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      в”Ӯ
