в•ӯв”Җ assistant [MainThread@2256878] в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•®
в”Ӯ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The user wants me to fix a crash in the LLVM SLP vectorizer. The crash is a verifier error, `Instruction does not dominate all uses!`, which indicates that the vectorizer is generating в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ invalid LLVM IR. This typically happens when an instruction is placed at a location where it does not dominate one of its uses, or when one of its operands does not dominate the        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ instruction itself.                                                                                                                                                                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The provided LLVM IR has a complex control flow graph, and the SLP vectorizer is attempting to vectorize `lcssa` PHI nodes in the `._crit_edge` block. The operands for these PHIs come  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ from multiple different predecessor blocks (`%5`, `%11`, `%6`, `%.lr.ph272.preheader`). This cross-block vectorization requires careful placement of the new vector instructions to      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ satisfy dominance rules.                                                                                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The function responsible for determining the insertion point is `SLPVectorizer::getInsertPoint`. The bug lies in this function's logic, which fails to find a valid insertion point in   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ this specific scenario. The core of the problem is that the chosen insertion point is not dominated by the definitions of all the scalar operands being vectorized.                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ To fix this, I will modify `getInsertPoint`. The correct logic should first establish a common dominator block for all the scalar operands. After finding this block, it should be used  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ as the insertion point. A safe and simple insertion point within this block is its terminator instruction. This ensures that the new vector instructions are placed after all scalar     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ operands within that block have been defined and before control flow leaves the block.                                                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ My patch will perform the following steps inside `getInsertPoint`:                                                                                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 1.  Initialize a `BasicBlock *Block` to `nullptr`.                                                                                                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 2.  Iterate through all scalar `Value *V` in the vectorization list `VL`.                                                                                                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 3.  If `V` is an `Instruction`, update `Block` to be the nearest common dominator of the current `Block` and the instruction's parent block. This is done using                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `DT.findNearestCommonDominator`.                                                                                                                                                         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 4.  After iterating through all operands, `Block` will hold a reference to a basic block that is dominated by the definitions of all instruction operands.                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 5.  The function will then return the terminator of this `Block` as the insertion point.                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ This approach guarantees that any new instruction inserted at this point will have all its scalar operands available, thus fixing the dominance violation. I will use `sed` to replace   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ the entire body of the `getInsertPoint` function with this new, correct implementation.                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ sed -i '/^Instruction \*SLPVectorizer::getInsertPoint(ArrayRef<Value \*> VL) const {$/,/^}$/c\                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ Instruction *SLPVectorizer::getInsertPoint(ArrayRef<Value *> VL) const {\                                                                                                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   BasicBlock *Block = nullptr;\                                                                                                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   for (Value *V : VL) {\                                                                                                                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ     if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {\                                                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       if (!Block)\                                                                                                                                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         Block = I->getParent();\                                                                                                                                                         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       else\                                                                                                                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         Block = DT.findNearestCommonDominator(Block, I->getParent());\                                                                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ     }\                                                                                                                                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   }\                                                                                                                                                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ \                                                                                                                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   if (!Block) {\                                                                                                                                                                         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ     for (Value *V : VL) {\                                                                                                                                                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       if (auto *A = dyn_cast<Argument>(V))\                                                                                                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         Block = &A->getParent()->getEntryBlock();\                                                                                                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ     }\                                                                                                                                                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   }\                                                                                                                                                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ \                                                                                                                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   if (!Block)\                                                                                                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ     return nullptr;\                                                                                                                                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ \                                                                                                                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   return Block->getTerminator();\                                                                                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ }' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                                                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      в”Ӯ
